-*- mode: org -*-

* --gateway
* cli
actually provide IPs
* --count
how many pings
* --all or --any or --half
By default, returns success if ANY ips are reachable.  --all switches to only
if all are reachable.  --half if at least half of the pings get a response.
* -d --dns
additionally use built-in IPs of Public DNS servers provided by...
* -e --exclude
do not ping specified IPs, even if they're specified (i.e., via the --dns built-ins)
